# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics and Speed Insights for the ERP system React/Vite project.

## What was implemented

### 1. Verified Package Installation
- Confirmed `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 is installed
- Confirmed `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 is installed
- Ran `npm install` to ensure all dependencies are properly installed

### 2. Configuration Changes
**Modified: `/src/main.jsx`**
- Added import for `SpeedInsights` component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the React root alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component
- Both components are properly placed within the StrictMode wrapper, following Vercel's official documentation

### 3. Implementation Details
According to the latest Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart and https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart):

**Web Analytics:**
- Already correctly configured with `<Analytics />` from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- Component properly placed at the root level of the application

**Speed Insights (NEW):**
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Enables automatic performance tracking for Core Web Vitals
- No additional configuration required

### 4. Testing
- Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
- No errors or warnings during the build process
- Production bundle size: 228.54 kB (gzipped: 68.84 kB)

## Project Details
- **Framework:** React 18.3.1 + Vite 5.4.2
- **Package Manager:** npm (package-lock.json)
- **Language:** JavaScript (JSX)
- **Structure:** Single Page Application with RTL (Arabic) support

## Notes
- The Analytics component was already present in the codebase, indicating that Web Analytics was partially configured
- Added Speed Insights to provide comprehensive performance monitoring
- Both tools will automatically begin tracking when the application is deployed to Vercel
- No environment variables or additional configuration files are required
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite applications

## Next Steps
When deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics → Enable)
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard (if not auto-enabled)
3. Data will automatically begin flowing to the dashboard after deployment
